content: Here is a comprehensive, legally-appropriate wedding photography contract for the details provided: Wedding Photography Contract This contract is entered into on [DATE] by and between Sarah Johnson Photography ("Photographer") and Kirmada ("Client"). Photography Services Photographer agrees to provide professional photography services for Client's wedding event on 9/30/2025 at the Jalandhar venue. Photographer will capture a minimum of 500 high-quality digital images using professional camera equipment. Package Details The Premium bachelors party package includes: - Up to 8 hours of photography coverage on the event date - All digital image files provided in high-resolution JPEG format - Online gallery for viewing and downloading images - Printing rights for personal use Payment Terms The total fee for the photography services is $999.99. A non-refundable retainer of 50% ($499.99) is due upon signing this contract. The remaining balance of $499.99 is due 30 days prior to the event date. Cancellation & Rescheduling If Client needs to cancel the event, the retainer fee is non-refundable. If the event is rescheduled with at least 90 days' notice, Photographer will transfer the retainer to the new date without penalty. Rescheduling with less than 90 days' notice will incur a $200 administrative fee. Image Delivery Photographer will deliver the final image files to Client within 4 weeks after the event date. Files will be available for download from the online gallery for 6 months. Copyright & Usage Rights The copyright and ownership of all images created by Photographer remains with Photographer. Client is granted a personal, non-exclusive license to print, share, and use the images for personal purposes. Commercial use of the images is prohibited without written permission from Photographer. Equipment & Backup Photographer will bring backup camera bodies, lenses, and lighting equipment to the event. In the unlikely event of equipment failure, Photographer will do their best to continue coverage using the backup gear. Professional Conduct Photographer agrees to provide friendly, courteous service and to respectfully comply with any reasonable requests from the Client or venue staff. Photographer retains creative control over the photography and posing during the event. By signing below, the parties agree to the terms of this Wedding Photography Contract. [Photographer Signature] Sarah Johnson, Sarah Johnson Photography [Client Signature] Kirmada

PHOTOGRAPHY SERVICE CONTRACT This Photography Service Contract ("Agreement") is made and entered into on [Current Date] by and between Sarah Johnson Photography ("Photographer") and piyush bday ("Client"). SERVICES The Photographer agrees to provide photography coverage for the Client's pre wedding shoot event ("Event") on Tuesday, September 30, 2025 at SHEMROCK. The Photographer will capture images using a variety of photography styles, including candid, posed, artistic, and documentary approaches. DELIVERABLES The Photographer will deliver high-resolution digital images from the Event. The Client will receive online gallery access and a print release allowing personal usage of the images. The Photographer will provide a minimum of 100 edited images within 4-8 weeks following the Event date. BUSINESS TERMS The Photographer maintains backup equipment and has contingency plans in place to ensure uninterrupted service. A second photographer can be provided at an additional fee if requested by the Client. For destination events, the Photographer's travel expenses will be reimbursed by the Client. In the event of inclement weather for outdoor events, the Photographer and Client will work together to reschedule or find an appropriate indoor location. The Photographer retains the copyright to all images captured during the Event. The Client is granted a personal, non-exclusive license to use the images for personal purposes. The Photographer may use the images for their portfolio, website, and social media, provided the Client is not individually identified without their consent. PROFESSIONAL STANDARDS The Photographer will dress professionally and conduct themselves in a courteous manner throughout the Event. The Photographer will coordinate with other vendors to ensure a smooth event flow and will accommodate a reasonable shot list provided by the Client. All images will be professionally edited and processed to the Photographer's high standards. PAYMENT TERMS The total fee for the Premium pre wedding shoot package is $1,000.00. A 50% deposit of $500.00 is due upon signing this Agreement, with the remaining balance of $500.00 due 14 days prior to the Event date. Payments can be made by cash, check, or online transfer. CANCELLATION AND RESCHEDULING If the Client cancels the Event, the deposit will be forfeited. If the Event is rescheduled more than 30 days in advance, the deposit can be applied to the new date. If the Event is rescheduled less than 30 days in advance, a new deposit will be required. In the event of a force majeure, such as natural disasters, pandemics, or other unforeseeable circumstances beyond the control of either party, the Photographer and Client will work together to reschedule the Event or provide a full refund of any payments made. LIABILITY AND INSURANCE The Photographer maintains professional liability insurance to cover any claims or damages that may arise from the provision of services. The Photographer is not responsible for lost, stolen, or damaged personal items belonging to the Client or their guests during the Event. This Agreement constitutes the entire understanding between the Photographer and the Client. Any modifications or amendments must be made in writing and signed by both parties.

PHOTOGRAPHY SERVICE CONTRACT This Photography Service Contract ("Agreement") is made and entered into on [Current Date] by and between Sarah Johnson Photography ("Photographer") and Piyush ("Client"). SERVICES Photographer agrees to provide photography services for Client's prewedding shool event on Tuesday, September 23, 2025 at Muskan ("Event"). Photographer shall capture digital images using a variety of photography styles, including candid, posed, artistic, and documentary approaches. Photographer will provide coverage for the duration of the Event. DELIVERABLES Photographer shall deliver to Client the following: - High-resolution digital images - Online gallery access for image viewing and selection - Print release and usage rights for all delivered images - Delivery of final edited images within 4-8 weeks after the Event The total number of edited images included in this package is [Agreed Upon Number]. BUSINESS TERMS 1. Equipment Backup and Contingency: Photographer maintains backup camera bodies, lenses, and other essential equipment to ensure uninterrupted coverage in the event of equipment failure. 2. Second Photographer: If deemed necessary by Photographer, a second photographer may be provided at no additional cost to Client. 3. Travel Considerations: For destination events, Photographer shall be reimbursed for all reasonable travel expenses, including transportation, accommodations, and meals. 4. Weather Contingencies: In the event of inclement weather that prevents outdoor photography, Photographer shall work with Client to adjust the photography plan and capture images in alternative indoor locations. 5. Copyright and Usage Rights: Photographer retains the copyright to all images captured during the Event. Client is granted a print release and the right to use the images for personal, non-commercial purposes. 6. Social Media and Portfolio Usage: Photographer reserves the right to use the images captured during the Event in Photographer's online portfolio, social media channels, and for other promotional purposes. PROFESSIONAL STANDARDS 1. Dress Code and Conduct: Photographer and any assisting personnel shall dress and conduct themselves in a professional manner throughout the Event. 2. Vendor Coordination: Photographer shall coordinate with other vendors (e.g., wedding planner, videographer) to ensure seamless event coverage. 3. Shot List and Special Requests: Photographer shall make reasonable efforts to accommodate Client's shot list and any special photography requests. 4. Post-Processing and Editing: Photographer shall apply professional post-processing and editing techniques to deliver high-quality, visually-appealing images. PAYMENT TERMS The total fee for Photographer's services is $1,000.00. A 50% deposit of $500.00 is due upon signing this Agreement, with the remaining balance of $500.00 due 14 days prior to the Event date. CANCELLATION AND RESCHEDULING In the event of cancellation by Client, the deposit shall be forfeited. If the Event is rescheduled, Photographer shall make reasonable efforts to accommodate the new date, subject to availability. If the rescheduled date is not acceptable to Photographer, the deposit shall be forfeited. FORCE MAJEURE If the Event is postponed or canceled due to circumstances beyond the control of either party, such as natural disasters, pandemics, or other acts of God, neither party shall be liable for any damages. In such cases, Photographer shall refund any prepaid amounts, less any expenses incurred. LIABILITY AND INSURANCE Photographer maintains professional liability insurance to cover any claims or damages that may arise from the provision of services. Photographer shall not be held liable for any injuries, losses, or damages that may occur during the Event, except in cases of gross negligence or willful misconduct. This Agreement constitutes the entire understanding between the parties. Any modifications or amendments must be made in writing and signed by both parties.
